					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">In &quot;roma.nes&quot; your vram updates are spilling into the frame, which is fine, since rendering is disabled. When you turn rendering back on you have to set the address to where you want the scroll. You can also wait until the next frame to turn it on.</div>

