			<td valign="top">
				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">IsharaComix wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><em>I shouldn't need to do this</em>.</div><br />You absolutely MUST reset the scroll after using $2006/$2007. The address register we access through $2006 is the same one the PPU uses to read data in order to draw the image. So if you leave that register pointing to same tile in the name tables, that's the point where rendering will start in the following frame. It is mandadory that you reset the scroll every frame at the end of your VBlank handler, so that rendering starts at the position you want to, not the last place you accessed with $2006/$2007.<br /><br />However, writing 0's to $2006 is NOT the proper way of resetting the scroll (that doesn't reset all the bits). You're supposed to use $2000 (to select the upper scrolling bits i.e. the name table) and $2005 (X and Y scroll).</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
